"title": "7304: anointing",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7304: anointing",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The application of oil was associated with times of rejoicing and celebration. It also possessed a deeper significance, including that of being singled out by God for special favour or responsibilities.</p>\n<h2>Anointing as a social custom</h2>\n<h3>In personal grooming</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:8\">ECC 9:8</a></strong> <em>The associations here are of joy and well-being.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth3:3\">RUT 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps92:10\">PSA 92:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:9\">ISA 57:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos6:6\">AMO 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:17\">MAT 6:17</a></p>\n<h3>Anointing guests as a mark of honour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:5\">PSA 23:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:36-Luke7:39\">LUK 7:36–7:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:44-Luke7:47\">LUK 7:44–7:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:3\">JHN 12:3</a></p>\n<h3>Anointing corpses as a burial preparation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:1\">MRK 16:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:6-Matt26:12\">MAT 26:6–26:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:38-John19:40\">JHN 19:38–19:40</a></p>\n<h2>Anointing religious objects</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:9-Exod40:11\">EXO 40:9–40:11</a></strong> <em>Anointed objects are set apart (consecrated), to be used only in the performance of religious ceremonies.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:18\">GEN 28:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:22-Exod30:33\">EXO 30:22–30:33</a></p>\n<h2>Anointing people for office</h2>\n<h3>Priests</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:12-Exod40:15\">EXO 40:12–40:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:16\">LEV 4:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:10-Lev21:12\">LEV 21:10–21:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:22\">1CH 29:22</a></p>\n<h3>Kings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:39\">1KI 1:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:1\">1SA 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:12-1Sam16:13\">1SA 16:12–16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:3\">2SA 5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:12\">2KI 11:12</a></p>\n<h3>A prophet</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:15-1Kgs19:16\">1KI 19:15–19:16</a> <em>the only reference to the anointing of a prophet</em></p>\n<h2>Anointing people for other purposes</h2>\n<h3>For purification</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:15-Lev14:18\">LEV 14:15–14:18</a></p>\n<h3>For healing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:13\">MRK 6:13</a></strong> <em>It has been suggested that anointing in a healing context may be related to the use of oil for medicinal purposes.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:14\">JAS 5:14</a></p>\n<h2>The figurative use of anointing</h2>\n<h3>Anointing by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:9\">1SA 26:9</a></strong> <em>Israel's king is frequently referred to as “the LORD's anointed”. His physical anointing is seen as symbolising a divine anointing. The word “Messiah” literally means “the anointed one”</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:1\">ISA 45:1</a></strong> <em>Cyrus, as God's agent for a specific task, is referred to as “his anointed”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:1\">2SA 23:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:2\">PSA 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:2\">PSA 45:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:20\">PSA 89:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:14\">EZK 28:14</a></p>\n<h3>God's people in the OT</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:22\">1CH 16:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:15\">PSA 105:15</a></p>\n<h3>Christian believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:21-2Cor1:22\">2CO 1:21–1:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:20\">1JN 2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:27\">1JN 2:27</a> <em>This anointing is not received in an outward ceremony but by sharing in the Holy Spirit's anointing of Jesus Christ.</em></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as God's Anointed One (the Messiah)</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:26-Acts4:27\">ACT 4:26–4:27</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ's receiving of the Holy Spirit at his baptism was his “anointing” for his Messianic work</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:38\">ACT 10:38</a></strong> <em>Note the link between anointing and the Holy Spirit.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:25-Dan9:26\">DAN 9:25–9:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:18\">LUK 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1\">ISA 61:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:9\">HEB 1:9</a></p>",
